Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 2026

Ad Analysis Tool ("we", "our", or "us") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting the personal data you share with us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, share, and protect your information when you use our services, including our website and application.

1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following information when you use our app or services:

Personal Information: Name, email address, and other contact information provided by you.
Facebook API Data: When you connect your Facebook account to our app, we collect and use data provided by Facebook, such as:
Public profile information (e.g., name, profile picture).
Ads data for analysis.
Usage Data: Information about how you interact with our app, including IP addresses, browser type, device type, and pages accessed.
2. How We Use Your Information
We may use the information we collect for the following purposes:

To provide, operate, and maintain our services.
To analyze ads data and generate market insights based on your request.
To improve our app, including user experience and functionality.
To respond to user requests, inquiries, and feedback.
3. How We Share Your Information
We do not sell or rent your personal data. However, we may share your information in the following circumstances:

Service Providers: We may share your data with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating our app, such as hosting services and analytics providers.
Legal Obligations: We may disclose your information when required to comply with a legal obligation, enforce our policies, or protect our rights.
4. Data Storage and Security
We store your data securely and use industry-standard measures to protect it from unauthorized access, disclosure, or modification. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Your Rights and Choices
You have the right to:

Access Your Data: Request access to the personal information we hold about you.
Update Your Data: Request corrections to any personal information that is inaccurate or outdated.
Delete Your Data: Request the deletion of your personal information. See Section 6 for how to request data deletion.
6. User Data Deletion
If you would like to delete your personal data, including any data collected through Facebook API, you can request deletion by contacting us at [your email/contact].

7. Third-Party Services and Links
Our app may include links to third-party websites or services. This Privacy Policy does not apply to those third-party services, and we encourage you to review their privacy policies.

8. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
Our app may use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance user experience, improve performance, and analyze traffic. You can choose to disable cookies through your browser settings.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the updated version will take effect immediately upon posting.

10. Contact Us
